of every single video.

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:48.000
It then automatically categorizes these videos
into three distinct tiers:

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:50.500
Viral, Mid, and Bombed.

00:00:50.500 --> 00:00:54.000
Now, you can clearly see the difference between
a video that gets five million views

00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:57.000
and one that barely breaks a million.

00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:01.000
Creator Luck distills this massive amount of data
into actionable insights.

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:05.000
You might hear gurus say that shorter titles are better —

00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:10.000
but our AI analysis proves that in this specific niche,
viral videos actually have titles

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:13.000
that are forty percent longer.

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:17.000
You'll also see that formatting your title as a question

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:20.000
significantly increases your chances of going viral.

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:23.000
You can even track creator velocity over time
on our interactive timeline,

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:25.000
seeing exactly when a channel started to take off.

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:29.000
But Creator Luck doesn't stop at dashboards.

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:31.500
